== Setup

Prerequisites: install git, clone this repo, then run:

  bash provision.sh          # full setup
  bash provision.sh --status # check what's installed

For Firefox extensions (Tree Style Tab, uBlock Origin):

  bash firefox_setup.sh

Tested on Ubuntu 24.04

== What gets installed

Shell:   zsh + oh-my-zsh + antigen + alien theme
Prompt:  powerline fonts (Ubuntu Mono for Powerline)
Tools:   fzf, eza, bat, rg, ag, autojump, vim, htop, xbindkeys
Python:  pip, virtualenv, virtualenvwrapper
Desktop: tilix (default terminal, dark mode), xbindkeys, pcmanfm
Configs: ~/.zshrc, ~/.xbindkeysrc, ~/.local/share/applications/pycharm.desktop

== Adding tools

Edit tools.list — each line defines one tool:
  type | name | source | check | description | depends | options

Supported types: apt, snap, github, url, script, manual

== Manual steps (after running scripts)

- Install PyCharm to ~/programy/pycharm/ (matches pycharm.desktop entry)
- Set terminal font to "Ubuntu Mono for Powerline"
- Add SSH key to GitHub: cat ~/.ssh/id_*.pub
